Josh Hawley (R-MO), whose support is crucial for a so-called budget reconciliation bill but is contingent on preserving Medicaid, wants to first see what House Republicans can muster through […]
title: Josh Hawley, drawing red line on Medicaid, is noncommittal on House’s Trump megabill

author: Mark Judge
description: One of my favorite places in my hometown of Washington, D.C. is the AFI Silver Theater in Silver Spring, Maryland. Every year, the AFI hosts wonderful film festivals featuring movies from Ireland, Africa, Iran, and other countries. They have festivals that feature certain directors of themes, such as the upcoming D.C. Labor Film Festival. So why not have an […]
title: Let’s have an anti-communist film festival

author: Mabinty Quarshie
description: As President Donald Trump works to secure multiple new trade deals that will benefit the United States, he has mostly taken to slamming his predecessor, former President Joe Biden, for the economic uncertainty that has swept the nation. The stock and bond markets have fluctuated due to Trump’s “Liberation Day” tariffs and subsequent 90-day pause. […]
title: Trump blames Biden for economy as pressure on tariff policy builds

author: Troy Edgar
description: The worst call you could ever receive as a parent is one telling you that your teenage son or daughter has been in a car crash. It’s a life-changing call that would go down as one of the worst days of your life. It could be even worse, though: What if you also found out […]
title: An illegal immigrant killed two teenagers in my community. Under the Trump administration, he will face justice

author: Maydeen Merino
description: As the United States seeks to reduce its reliance on foreign entities for rare earths and critical minerals, an unexpected solution may lie in coal plants’ landfills. The U.S. imports nearly all its critical minerals and rare earths, relying particularly on China. Other countries boast lower-cost production, greater mineral abundance, and fewer permitting challenges. However, […]
title: Could coal plant landfills be the answer to the rare earths supply problem?

author: Lauren Green
description: House Republicans on Tuesday will seek to reverse the trend of rising Medicaid spending with reforms some fiscal hawks say don’t go far enough and Democrats have decried as too harsh. The House Energy and Commerce Committee will hold a markup hearing Tuesday afternoon on a significant healthcare section of President Donald Trump’s agenda, which […]
title: House GOP’s Medicaid reforms will be hashed out in public

author: Washington Examiner
description: Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent announced a welcome pause in the Trump administration’s trade wars Sunday. A preliminary agreement with China will reduce U.S. tariffs on most Chinese imports from 145% to 30%, with a reciprocal reduction on U.S. exports to China from 125% to 10%. The reprieve is set to last only 90 days, however, […]
title: A welcome de-escalation in the China trade war

author: Brady Knox
description: President Donald Trump is throwing his support behind former New Jersey Assemblyman Jack Ciattarelli in the state’s 2025 gubernatorial election. In a lengthy Truth Social post on Monday, Trump granted Ciattarelli his “Complete and Total Endorsement,” celebrating him as a “WINNER” who “WILL NOT LET YOU DOWN.” “Jack Ciattarelli is a terrific America First Candidate […]
title: Trump backs Jack Ciattarelli in coveted New Jersey governor race

author: David Sivak
description: Senate Democrats will be protesting President Donald Trump‘s decision to accept a luxury jet from Qatar, a gift that has raised ethics and national security concerns from lawmakers of both parties. In the coming days, Sen. Brian Schatz (D-HI) will introduce a resolution disapproving of the gift, a Boeing 747 that Trump wants to replace Air Force One. […]
title: Senate Democrats promise to ‘take action’ over Trump accepting Qatari luxury jet

author: Brady Knox
description: Democratic National Committee Vice Chairman David Hogg accused the organization of trying to remove him from his position. On Monday, Hogg announced that the DNC commenced an effort to fast-track his removal as vice chairman. title: David Hogg says DNC in process of removing him as vice chairman

author: Samantha-Jo Roth
description: Israeli American advocates and the family of a freed Israeli hostage are sounding the alarm over President Donald Trump’s willingness to accept a “free” luxury jet from Qatar, pointing to the country’s close relationship with Iran and its long-standing support for Hamas leaders.  While the release of Israeli American Edan Alexander on Monday after more […]
title: Pro-Israel Americans urge Trump to ‘tread lightly’ with Qatar

author: Brady Knox
description: Trump administration officials have welcomed the first batch of white South African refugees into the United States. title: Trump officials celebrate white South Africans’ arrival in DC
